[I] Antlr C++ runtime

[T] ANTLR (ANother Tool for Language Recognition) is a powerful parser
[T] generator for reading, processing, executing, or translating structured
[T] text or binary files. It's widely used to build languages, tools, and
[T] frameworks. From a grammar, ANTLR generates a parser that can build and
[T] walk parse trees.

[U] https://www.antlr.org/

[A] Terence Parr
[M] andrei32

[C] extra/base
[F] CROSS OBJDIR

[L] BSD
[V] 4.13.2
[P] X -----5---9 200.000

[D] 3829e81c64a48392fba162fcda4423b5b1d5e00466df31e72b0595be antlr4-cpp-runtime-4.13.2-source.zip https://www.antlr.org/download/

var_append cmakeopt ' ' -DCMAKE_POLICY_VERSION_MINIMUM=3.5
var_append cmakeopt ' ' '-DANTLR_BUILD_CPP_TESTS=OFF -DBUILD_GMOCK=OFF'
